{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, modern LLMs can generate high-quality reasoning steps to explain their predictions [33,71], improving performance in few-shot or zero-shot learning [33,68,71] and serving as self-improvement data [28,79].",
    "However, LLMs' size hinders their deployment in practice.",
    "Correspondingly, recent research explores leveraging generated rationales for training smaller, task-specific models with minimal computational and memory overhead [23,35,43,69].",
    "For example, PINTO [68] presents an LLM pipeline that rationalizes via prompt-based learning.",
    "However, they still rely on an LLM for rationale generation at test-time, not fully addressing deployment challenges."
  ],
